#!/usr/bin/env python3

import sys
import os

# Check if file exists
if os.path.exists('stock.xlsx'):
    print("File exists, size:", os.path.getsize('stock.xlsx'))
else:
    print("File does not exist")
    sys.exit(1)

# Try to read with different methods
try:
    import pandas as pd
    print("pandas imported successfully")
    
    # Try reading the Excel file
    df = pd.read_excel('stock.xlsx')
    print("Excel file read successfully")
    print("DataFrame shape:", df.shape)
    print("DataFrame:")
    print(df)
    print("\nColumn names:")
    print(df.columns.tolist())
    
except ImportError as e:
    print(f"Import error: {e}")
except Exception as e:
    print(f"Error reading Excel: {e}")
    
    # Try alternative approach
    try:
        import xlrd
        print("Trying with xlrd...")
        df = pd.read_excel('stock.xlsx', engine='xlrd')
        print("DataFrame:")
        print(df)
    except Exception as e2:
        print(f"xlrd also failed: {e2}")
        
        # Try with openpyxl
        try:
            df = pd.read_excel('stock.xlsx', engine='openpyxl')
            print("Success with openpyxl:")
            print(df)
        except Exception as e3:
            print(f"openpyxl also failed: {e3}")
